---
import Article from '../layouts/Article.astro';

const title = 'Funscript editor - a frame-accurate, multi-axis editor in FunGen';
const description =
  'FunGen is a full funscript editor: a frame-accurate multi-axis timeline, transforms and pipelines, chapters, unlimited undo/redo, and the Doctor quality checks. Free to use.';
const canonicalPath = '/funscript-editor';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

const articleLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'The FunGen funscript editor',
  description,
  inLanguage: 'en',
  dateModified: '2026-07-17',
  mainEntityOfPage: 'https://fungen.app/funscript-editor',
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'FunGen' },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'FunGen',
    logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: 'https://fungen.app/icon-512.png' },
  },
};
const breadcrumbs = [{ name: 'Funscript editor', path: '/funscript-editor' }];
---

<Article
  {title}
  {description}
  heading="The funscript editor in FunGen"
  {canonicalPath}
  {articleLd}
  {breadcrumbs}
>
  <p class="lead">
    FunGen isn't only an AI generator - it's a full <strong>funscript editor</strong>. Build a script
    by hand on a frame-accurate timeline, or clean up what the AI generated, and play it straight to
    your device, without switching tools. The editor is free to use.
  </p>

  <h2>A frame-accurate, multi-axis timeline</h2>
  <p>
    Edit against the video frame by frame: add, move and tune points, set a point to an exact height
    with a number key, or pull the nearest point to the playhead and set it in one keystroke. Every
    axis - stroke plus roll, pitch, surge, sway, twist - gets its own track, and you can overlay one
    axis on another to line them up.
  </p>

  <h2>Transforms, plugins and pipelines</h2>
  <p>
    Reshape a whole selection or the entire script with dozens of one-click transforms and plugins:
    amplitude, smoothing, speed limits, timing, and more. Chain your favourites into a
    <strong>pipeline</strong> and run a full cleanup in a single click - autotune, reshape, limit.
  </p>

  <h2>Chapters, bookmarks and a workflow that remembers</h2>
  <p>
    Split a long scene into named, colour-coded chapters, drop bookmarks with one key, and reopen
    right where you left off. <strong>Undo and redo are unlimited and survive closing and reopening</strong>
    a project, so your edit history is never lost. FunGen also opens <code>.funscript</code> and
    <code>.fungen</code> files directly on Windows, macOS and Linux.
  </p>

  <h2>The Doctor: know it's ready</h2>
  <p>
    Before you ship a script, the <strong>Funscript Doctor</strong> gives it a device-aware quality
    score from 0 to 100 - flagging speed violations, off-frame points, dead zones, jitter and missing
    strokes, and fixing most of them in one click. It's the difference between a script that looks
    right on the timeline and one that actually feels right on the hardware.
  </p>

  <h2>Generate, then refine</h2>
  <p>
    The fastest workflow is both halves together: let the AI
    <a href={`${base}/generate-funscripts-from-video/`}>generate a funscript from your video</a>, then
    polish it in the editor. New to the format? Start with
    <a href={`${base}/what-is-a-funscript/`}>what a funscript is</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a href={`${base}/`}>Download FunGen</a> - the editor, player and library are free; full-quality AI
    generation is the Pro unlock.
  </p>
</Article>
